FORGEZERO TOML CONFIGURATION
============================

ForgeZero supports project configuration in TOML, YAML, and their .yml variants.
TOML is the recommended format for new projects because it is explicit, easy to
read, and works well with generated files.

MINIMAL EXAMPLE
---------------
output = "app"
mode = "auto"
profile = "balanced"

[flags]
cc = ["-O2"]
ld = ["-Wl,--gc-sections"]

COMMON KEYS
-----------
output
    The default output name.
mode
    Link strategy: auto, c, or raw.
profile
    Named profile preset.
target
    Cross-compilation triple.
debug
    Emit debug symbols.
verbose
    Print executed commands.
no_cache
    Disable incremental caching.
include
    Include other config files.
variables
    Named variables exposed to configure.fz.
flags.cc
    Extra C/C++ compiler flags.
flags.ld
    Extra linker flags.

INCLUDES
--------
include = ["base.toml", "common/build.toml"]

Included files are resolved relative to the including file and merged before
the active project config is validated.

RUNTIME OVERRIDE EXAMPLE
------------------------
fz --config .fz.toml --set output=myapp --set mode=raw
